  "text": "Immunohistology was performed as described previously. [CITATION_1] 52 Briefly, OCT-embedded frozen tissue or threedimensional collagen gels were sectioned, and the slides were fixed in 2% paraformaldehyde and permeabilized with for 0.5% Triton X-100 in phosphate-buffered saline (PBS) for 10 minutes at room temperature. The slides were blocked with appropriate serum (5% in PBS) for 1 hour at room temperature. Subsequently, the slides were incubated for 1 hour at room temperature with primary antibodies followed by incubation of appropriate secondary antibody for 1 hour at room temperature. After staining the slides were mounted with mounting media (Vector Laboratories, Burlingame, CA), and examined using a fluorescence microscope.",
